    {
      "id": 17,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        -900,
        60
      ],
      "size": [
        620,
        540
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 26,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# Anima Hires-Fix + Pose / Depth control\n\n**Flow:** reference images -> DWPose / Depth Anything V2 -> Anima LLLite Pose -> Anima LLLite Depth -> first pass -> ESRGAN 1.5x -> second pass.\n\n## Use\n1. Upload a pose reference to **Pose reference**.\n2. Upload a depth/composition reference to **Depth reference**. The same photo may be used for both.\n3. Edit the prompt and queue. Preview nodes show the actual control maps.\n\n## Starting controls\n- Pose: strength 1.0, active 0.00-0.80.\n- Depth: strength 0.65, active 0.00-0.70.\n- Controls affect the first pass only. The 0.45-denoise second pass redraws detail while preserving its latent structure.\n- If anatomy becomes rigid, lower Depth first. If the pose is weak, raise Pose gradually.\n\n## Requirements\n- kohya-ss/ComfyUI-Anima-LLLite compatibility node.\n- comfyui_controlnet_aux.\n- anima-lllite-pose-1 and anima-lllite-depth-1 under models/controlnet.\n\nThe repository prestartup hook installs these dependencies automatically for direct-clone and baked ComfyUI images.\n\n> Pose/Depth are Preview3 sample patches. They run on Anima Base v1.0 with reduced quality; Pose is a soft prior, not a strict lock."
      ],
      "color": "#222",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    },
